The course gives a short overview on different materials and their importance for functioning of the modern technological society (construction materials, materials for energetics and information technologies, materials technologies), introduces the coming special courses and lecturers. Visits are planned to materials-related research labs and companies. The students will compile and present a short review on a course-related topic.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goals of the course are: 1. Introduction to materials science and technologies in historical and applied aspects. 2. Introduction of special courses and lecturers. 3. Introduction to materials research in Estonia. 4. Introduction to laboratories and companies related to materials science and technology as places for completing study projects and degree papers and as prospective employers.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student, after passing the course 1. Has general ideas on achievements, problems and development in materials science and technology. 2. Has an overview on materials-related research in Estonia and on some enterprises in Tartu of respective profile, is able to use this information for planning his/her studies and for orientation on job market. 3. Is able to present a short written summary on site visits to research labs / enterprises of the corresponding profile.
